thread.title: Helias blanks Quincy in volleyball

author: News Tribune
title: Helias blanks Quincy in volleyball
text:
Share 
QUINCY, Ill. — The Helias volleyball team wrapped up its regular season with a straight-set win Saturday at Quincy (Ill.): 25-15, 25-23. 
Ashley Dudenhoeffer had 23 assists, 15 digs, six service points and three kills. Hannah Borchelt and Hannah Eynard each had seven kills, and Suzie Kuensting had seven service points and six kills. Blake Berhorst had 13 digs and Ellie Rockers added four blocks. 
Helias (28-3-1) begin district-tournament play at 5 p.m. Tuesday at Blair Oaks. 
The Lady Crusaders’ JV team wrapped up its season with a 25-23, 25-16 victory. Riley Bernskoetter had 14 assists and nine service points. Amie Henson had 11 assists and eight service points. Callie Henson led with eight kills while Regan Bruns and Kelsey Brester had five apiece. Bradi Berhorst notched 17 digs. The JV team ends the year 27-3-2. 
The freshman squad wrapped up an undefeated season with a 25-15, 25-13 win. Krystal Brauner had seven service points and eight digs. Jada Oldham had 10 assists and six service points. Olivia Farrow had eight digs and six service points. Danielle Kroll had six kills and Reagan Bernskoetter had five. Sommer Kolb had eight assists, while Grace Millard tallied two blocks. The freshmen set a school record with their 32 wins, losing just three sets all season. ﻿
